    <title>Notes on the behavior of the Ratliff-Rush filtration</title>
    <summary>  We establish new classes of Ratliff-Rush closed ideals and some pathological
behavior of the Ratliff-Rush closure. In particular, Ratliff-Rush closure does
not behave well under passage modulo superficial elements, taking powers of
ideals, associated primes, leading term ideals, and the minimal number of
generators. In contrast, the reduction number of the Ratliff-Rush filtration
behaves better: it preserves some information on the reduction number of the
ideal.
</summary>
